Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Bank PHB, University Press of Nigeria

-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 
2011-07-04T15:28:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-bank-phb-stanbic-ibtc-bank-of-nigeria.html
Namibia’s FTSE/ Namibia Overall Index (FTN098) 
rose for the seventh day, the longest winning streak since the
seven days through March 25, increasing 0.2 percent to 857.05 by
the 4 p.m. end of trading in  Windhoek .  The Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index retreated for a
second day, slipping 0.6 percent to 24,536.96 by the 2:30 p.m.
close in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement from the
bourse. Kenya’s All-Share Index advanced 0.2 percent to 70.50 by
the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi. Mauritius’s SEMDEX Index climbed
0.1 percent to 2,098.49 by the 1:30 p.m. close in  Port Louis .
The Ghana Stock Exchange Composite Index was little changed at
1,188.79 by the 3 p.m. close in Accra.  The following shares rose or fell in sub-Saharan  Africa ,
excluding  South Africa . Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Bank PHB Plc (PLATINUM)  , a Nigerian lender bailed out by
the central bank in 2009, lost 4 kobo, or 4.7 percent, to 82
kobo, its biggest decline since June 14, after net income
dropped to 96.96 million naira ($634,866) for the three months
through March, compared with 2.75 billion naira a year earlier,
the Lagos-based company said in a statement.  University Press Plc (UPL)  , a Nigerian  book publisher ,
fell 23 kobo, or 4.4 percent, to 5 naira, after full-year profit
for the 12 months through March retreated to 211.38 million
naira compared with 276.82 million naira a year earlier, the
Ibadan-based company said in a statement after the market closed
on July 1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
